{"title":"Petitions and campaigns","public_updated_at":"2016-10-07T13:45:02Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>If you wish to petition the government online, more information can be found at <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/petition-government\">Petition the government</a>.</p>\n\n<p>If you wish to contact the Department for Communities and Local Government direct you can do so in the following ways.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"electronically\">Electronically</h3>\n<p>Please use our <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://forms.communities.gov.uk/\">webform</a>.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"by-post\">By post</h3>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nDepartment for Communities and Local Government \n<br>Fry Building \n<br>2 Marsham Street \n<br>London \n<br>SW1P 4DF\n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h3 id=\"by-hand\">By hand</h3>\n\n<p>If you would like to hand deliver a petition, please contact the department prior to your arrival on 030 3444 0000 to make sure that you can hand in your petition to 2 Marsham Street security personnel.</p>\n\n<p>We publish our responses to petitions and campaigns that have been sent direct by post or email to the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p>\n\n<p>As we receive a large volume of correspondence in connection with campaigns, we may not always send individual responses.</p>\n\n<p>When you send us your petition or campaign correspondence you must make it clear if you do not want details of your petition or campaign, or our response, to be published online (even without names and addresses of the petitioners).</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"responses-to-recent-petitions\">Responses to recent petitions</h3>\n\n<p>Our responses to some recent petitions and campaigns are given below.</p>\n\n<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1985488\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/595956/170224_Letter_re_Local_Housing